{"type":"message","id":"27f4ed85","parentId":"58f9f8d7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T05:27:55.293Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now I have all the provider info. Let me write a comprehensive test script. The sub-agent failed because it tried to use the model but got 401 errors - likely because the API key was invalid or the endpoint was wrong. Let me run the tests myself using curl.\n\nKey findings:\n- **deepseek**: baseUrl=https://api.deepseek.com, key=***..., models: deepseek-chat, deepseek-v4-flash\n- **ollama-pay**: baseUrl=https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1, key=***..., many models\n- **ollama-claude**: baseUrl=https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/anthropic, key=***..., models for claude-style\n\n\n- **openai**: baseUrl=https://api.openai.com/v1, key is empty, which explains the 401 errors\n- **openai-codex**: baseUrl=https://chatgpt.com/backend-api, key starts with eyJhb..., models: gpt-5.5, gpt-5.4-mini\n- **minimax**: baseUrl=https://api.minimax.io/anthropic, key=***..., models: MiniMax-M2.7, MiniMax-M2.7-Lightning, MiniMax-VL-01\n\nNow I'll write a test script that covers all these endpoints with proper authentication.","thinkingSignature":"d4938e533dd93b67bb0ae26e56b049f7ae13500b13043ca42010bf1e1a5a3ef6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ctx2fgjtgjxy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json, subprocess, concurrent.futures, time\n\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\nproviders = d.get('models', {}).get('providers', {})\n\n# Build test list: (provider_name, base_url, api_key, model_id)\ntests = []\nfor name, p in providers.items():\n    base = p.get('baseUrl', '')\n    key = p.get('apiKey', '')\n    for m in p.get('models', []):\n        tests.append((name, base, key, m['id']))\n\nprint(f\"Total models to test: {len(tests)}\")\nprint()\n\ndef test_model(args):\n    prov, base, key, model = args\n    if not base or not key:\n        return prov, model, \"❌\", \"No baseUrl or apiKey\"\n    try:\n        import urllib.request, urllib.error\n        payload = json.dumps({\"model\": model, \"messages\": [{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"hi\"}], \"max_tokens\": 5}).encode()\n        req = urllib.request.Request(base + \"/chat/completions\", data=payload, headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}, method=\"POST\")\n        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=15)\n        code = resp.getcode()\n        return prov, model, \"✅\", f\"HTTP {code}\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return prov, model, \"❌\", f\"HTTP {e.code}\"\n    except Exception as ex:\n        return prov, model, \"❌\", str(ex)[:50]\n\nresults = []\nwith concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=8) as ex:\n    futs = {ex.submit(test_model, t): t for t in tests}\n    for fut in concurrent.futures.as_completed(futs):\n        results.append(fut.result())\n\n# Sort by provider\nresults.sort(key=lambda x: (x[0], x[1]))\nfor prov, model, status, err in results:\n    print(f\"{status} {prov}/{model} | {err}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":770,"output":809,"cacheRead":28608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30187,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778131658451,"responseId":"064b55cbe2b3d90824d9ff10fa078ae4"}}
